name: Steph
bio: published wedding photographer. Digital and Film. Documentary approach. Editorial feel.

social_posts.post_text:
My last wedding of 2022 🥹 and it was magical with Taylor and Tyler. It truly felt like one big hangout with the best group of friends and family. It was so intimate and so incredibly intentional. I feel so lucky to have ended on this high note. I love ya both so stinkin much! 

It was really hard to pick the photos to post. Typically I go hard on the posed because I love that part of the day and working with my couple creatively but I thought it would be fun to go a little heavier on the candids of the day 💕

Part 1 of Kate and Ross in NYC. 

I remember when I moved to the city and experienced my first Christmas, it was magical. Truly indescribable. I’m actually quite the sap for Christmas. Give me all the traditions, cringey lifetime movies, nostalgic decor and music, I’m here for it. And NYC will always be my favorite place for Christmas. 

One of my favorite memories was when my husband and I would walk around at night past all of the tree stands. Just along the side of the roads. So normal for a native New Yorker but so inspiring for me. 

In true FTD fashion that visual memory stuck with me and I have been wanting to shoot this concept for a while. Dragging a Christmas tree throughout the mundane NYC areas with Christmas lights. 

Had the best team by my side to execute: @natalieejogray with the styling. @sparkskatelyn @ross__newhouse being the absolute best muses 🤤and of course my incredible assistant @carterperry.co along side helping me make sure it all went so smoothly. Excited to share more of these and my twist on a Christmas shoot 🎄

Part 2 of Kate and Ross in the city. This chunk I had to share of my film shots 🤭 excited to incorporate more in 2023. 

Currently back in my cozy little hometown with family and it’s so lovely. Merry Christmas everyone 🎄
A second little snip from Kait and JJ’s engagement session at their home in Denver.

Ok I’ve had a long enough break from weddings now and I’m ready for my 2023 season! My first wedding of the year will be in Nola in February and I can’t wait to show you! 

Ps, if you wanna see this full gallery check out the link in my story right now!

A few of my favs from shooting with Reed and Nick while I was in Arizona. 

This session was so simple and really challenged me with posing which I love. The location wasn’t anything special, as you can see it was quite literally a dirt lot. I wanted to work with the harsh light to really emphasize contrast for this and we all know I love blue skies. 

I also want to add, these jeans were $5 from a second hand store, the bra was $10 from jc penny, and the location was free. You can absolutely elevate your couples sessions and they won’t cost you hundreds of dollars! 

I had so much fun shooting with Reed and Nick and I can’t wait to share more 💕
Did some updated branding shots. Here’s a little snip of it.

Some western elements mixed with a dash of chic vibes from last fall.

My talented team of vendors: 
Florals: @flowerdisco_ 
Table styling : @rivieracreative_ 
Clothing: @natalieejogray 
Paper goods: @bareinkco 
Models: @jordandunning_
A few of my favorite snips from Gabby and Jake’s backyard wedding in NY 😎

Sharing a few of my favs from my time spent with Jonnie and Garrett in Arizona. 

I really loved this shoot for so many reasons but particularly because of the location. My friend recently bought a home and it needs a little tlc. I told him I didn’t want him to touch a single thing because being challenged by your environment is one of my favorite things to work with and this mentality is truly becoming the foundation of my work: To create art within any environment. 

Styling: @natalieejogray 
Edited with @fromthedaisiespresets

HEY wedding photographers, I created something big for you 🥰 it’s a long read but trust me, check it out. 

Want 5 New Inquiries In Only 5 Days? 

Want To Be Published By Junebug Weddings? 

📣 Want All Of This... For FREE? 📣

I am hosting a “Thrive To Five” new inquiries marketing challenge along with 12 other amazing photography educators on February 27th

I partnered with @junebugweddings just so we could make this the BIGGEST event of the year for wedding photographers.

Along with Junebug, hear from speakers such as Laurken Kendall, Kaley From Kansas, Rocky Mountain Bride, Catalina Jean, and SO MANY MORE!!!!

Register by clicking the link in my bio 🥰

And join me and my team LIVE tomorrow @ 5:30 PM PST in my FB group where I will be talking about all of the event details.

What can you expect from the Thrive To Five Challenge?

🌼 12 wedding photography educators teaching on all topics such as free marketing strategies, vendor relationships, and how to get published.
🌼 Workbooks + PDFs to hold yourself accountable to hitting 5 new inquiries in only 5 days.
🌼 LIVE Q&As with the speakers every day of the challenge.... and so much more!!

Comment “I’m in!” once you’ve registered for the challenge so I can keep an eye out for you! 

Okay, love ya! 

-Steph 😘

One of my favorite shoots with one of my favorite couples. 

I loved this so much because of the simplicity. We all know I loveee playing with objects and busy environments but the challenge of having absolutely nothing except my couple was really inspiring. 

Ps Kelsey is an incredibleeee videographer, so check her out @kpvisuals__
Sharing some film from Taylor and Tyler’s wedding in Joshua tree.

Sharing some film shots from Tori and Bear’s wedding in New Orleans. I decided to go with film first. I really love the different ways to aesthetically capture the moments. It’s really inspiring to me. Excited to be offering this at all my weddings. 

I loveddd this wedding. I connected with Bear and Tori what felt like forever ago at their engagements and have been anxiously waiting their day ever since. Their focus was definitely their friends and family coming together and their whole day was so focused on that. Leading with a live local band and ending with a second line down to the bars.  Made for the best reception. This was my first wedding in NOLA and it was truly so incredible to witness the culture. Feeling extra thankful for the experiences I get to witness. 💕

Keep a peep for something even more exciting for my weddings to come🫣🤭

Something about camcorder footage is so inspiring to me and just gives me a completely different perspective visually. 

I’m so excited to be adding this as an option for my clients to have. Get ready to see more from me this year 💕
6pm in New York.

Part 1 with Julie and Zane at their engagement session. 

I had a lot of fun with Julie and Zane. They were so easy and fun to experiment with. These two are long time burning man goers and really appreciate the unique aspect of art, and really life in general, so I knew we had to do something fun. (Also put some feelers out we’re able to snag BM tickets this year, k?, thanks) 

I love mixing different types of aesthetics. This grungy run down warehouse was the perfect mix with their pastel vintage clothing. It truly was a crackhouse chic moment in the best way 😂 

Cannot wait to capture their funky day in a few months 😍

One of my favorite sessions I’ve done. 

I really love the simplicity of the session and rather the lack of props yet this session feels really styled. My incredible florist @flowerdisco_ made these crowns with florals she sourced from the side of the road. The location was a spot I found behind a venue. The styling wasn’t anything over the top yet so curated. Thanks my girl @nataliegraycreative 

It’s so important to me to be able to provide an artful session for my clients but also so specifically intended for them.

Sharing a few snips of Mack and Kyle from my teachings at the @boldandbrazenworkshop workshop. 

Emma asked me to be apart of her workshop and wow, I cannot wait to show you guys more. This girl is so detail oriented and has the most incredible team along side her making her visions come to life. 

I really like this sessions because my group was supposed to be shooting at the very beautiful pool set up, but in true FTD fashion I wanted to challenge my group to see beauty in a different location. So I dragged them to the dirty roof. 

It’s truly been such an honor to be able to be apart of this and provide value to the attendees. If they can take away one thing from me to implement in their business, I call it a win 💕

Sharing a few from this very chic and elegant session. I think what I loved most about this one was showing the attendees how to incorporate intimate posing and challenging them to slow down and have unique eyes when it comes to capturing a wedding day. 

I have my next wedding of the year down in NOLA in two weeks and I cannot wait to create there again!

Ps how incredible was the styling by @marialimon_? Her and @theboldamericana created such a vision 😍

Balance… it’s one of those words that we all like to use, yet most of us don’t feel like we’ve actually achieved. Or let’s be honest, most of feel like “balance” is a pie in the sky dream that doesn’t really exist. 

Years ago when I first started running different companies I realized (after burning myself out) that I only had so much energy to go around, and the people who mattered most to me were NOT the ones getting the best parts of me, they basically got leftovers every night… and who really feels taken care of when it’s leftovers every night? 

Today on @thelandlockedmermaidpodcast I’m chatting with goddess @fromthedaisies about what running a household AND a 6 figure company really looks like and how she’s consciously making decisions to put her family first and how she’s doing it. 

Show Steph some love below, and share your thoughts with us below! ❤️❤️ #podcast #motherhood #balancingact #womeninbusiness #womenartists

Part 1 of Austin and Tyle’s engagement session. 

They met me out in central Illinois while I was visiting my parents. We played with all those Midwest vibes and I’m so excited to share more. They loved the session I did in my grandparents home that was empty and very outdated so momma had to deliver. Peep the last video of me exploring this nasty af trailer that’s been sitting empty for over a year. But it was perfect 😍 

Stay tuned for more spots we explored 💕 so in love with these angels already! 

Edited with @fromthedaisiespresets

Sharing some film from Mac and Kyle on the farm in San Miguel. 

I mean would it be a FTD vibe if we didn’t have an undie moment? But really I loved having Mac get in undies for this. It really added a level of intimacy and connection. 

I shot this entire series on film and it gave me all those butterflies of not knowing exactly how it will turn out. This session was meant to be a time filler during the actual styled session Emma envisioned for her workshop but this turned out to be my favorite. Such beauty in the simple. 

This year my engagement sessions are all over the place with some being so styled and out of the box but also so many that are simple and sweet. This year is just already filling me to the top. 💕

Had the best time in NOLA this weekend and while I was there I was lucky enough to shoot Lansa and Quentin.

I knew I wanted a location that was really reflective of the vibe of NOLA. Lansa and Quentin were the absolute best best besttttt to shoot with and I can’t wait to share more from my time with them.
Sharing a tiny tiny preview of the camcorder footage from Kait and JJ’s wedding in NOLA. 💕

A mix of film and digital bridal getting ready photos with Kait. 

Shooting in bathrooms with my clients is becoming quite the personality trait for me but I’m loving every minute of it 😂 this was such a fun way to spice up Kait’s bridal portraits while getting ready. Really excited to share more from their day in NOLA. 

Also how incredible are these florals by @crybabyfloral 💕

Every year me and my girls go to NY to do a little creation together before our wedding season gets too crazy and this was a little snip of it. 

Steph is truly such a floral artist. When I told her I wanted florals on the windows she knew exactly how to create something so complimentary of the space. Keely worked along side us for this one and included her incredible skills with table scapes. It was really fun to challenge myself with those details. Her eye for the little pieces that brought the whole table together is just unmatched. And of course my girl nat just nails it with the chic styling I wanted for this one. She so flawlessly complimented Eden and Deidre’s natural styles. Speaking of …. Can we take a moment of silence for these two?! Honored to had made some magic together. If you don’t follow them, do it. Both are also such talented creatives. 

K that’s it for now. As always, thanks for following along 💕💕

I struggle badly thinking how this summer won’t look like last, and next summer won’t look anything like this years. I do not handle my babies growing up well. It’s gut wrenching honestly. Which is odd, because what a blessing it is to watch them grow. Motherhood is the most beautiful gift I’ve ever been given. Yet so painful at the same time. That’s the only way I know how to explain it. A love so deep it can’t be described.

I went into this shoot last minute deciding I wanted the entire thing to be in film. No regrets. 

The harsh light was a must for me. Can you tell I’m loving it lately? This shoot was so simple and so relaxed. This city is so inspiring to me and I’m excited to be back in just a few short months to shoot some incredible clients of mine.
Bri and Ben pre sweet little baby.

Had to share more from my honeys engagement session. I loved this spot so much. This was actually my home town bowling alley growing up but now it’s vacant. There were a set of old chairs from inside so strategically placed on the side of the building, clearly asking for me to shoot with them … obviously. It was so fun to play with the empty space that complimented the area so well.

Part 1 of Joss and Katerina’s elopement in Copenhagen. 

Their elopement was so intimate and entirely based around them. I forgot how special elopement’s are because of that reason. Both of the girls showed such a deep love for one another and it was truly so beautiful to be apart of. 

Here’s just a few favs. A mix between film and digital. Also fun fact, I shot most of this session with flash 🫢 my favorite little element to add during harsh light as well. Excited to share more soon ❤️

It’s the details for me 🤤

Can’t believe it’s taken me so long to post from this wedding. Alex is a talented videographer herself and as artists it’s always such a compliment to be hired by someone else in the industry. Their wedding was full of that yummy Spanish detail that floods Taos. The whole vendor team brought their vision to life in such a magical way. Another highlight was their friend group because we liveeee for a good reception dance floor

This was part of my Illinois content retreat and this session had three parts (stay tuned because it’s pretty amazing) but a big reason I chose to do central Illinois is because I grew up here. Literally. This was shot 2 minutes from my childhood home. Chillicothe babyyyy. But this place is so special to me and I wanted to make a point that the most beautiful things can be created in areas where we aren’t custom to thinking are “beautiful”

We grew up in the middle of no where. What was internet? The country roads surrounded by corn fields are so inspiring to me. Maybe it’s the nostalgia. But I thought, what a perfect place to set up a dance floor with a very chic looking bride and groom. So that’s what we did. Classic FTD move I know. Just here to remind you that your wedding day can truly look however you want it to. 

Stayed tuned for the session at the church because momma is bringing back the church vibes. #gogreyghosts

A few of my favorite shots from our time spent with Sara and Dee. 

There was something about this abandoned trailer with the afternoon light that hits so perfectly. It’s been sitting empty in the country for as long as I can remember and it has always brought me inspiration for a couples shoot. 

I wanted to use this shoot as a challenge for my attendees to not use props but rather the environment around them for posing and direction, of which, they nailed it. 

Ps, can we all give @nataliegraycreative some love for turning these carhartt overalls into a dress for Sara 🫡

Whoever said traditional church weddings aren’t a vibe lied. Let me prove that beauty in this industry can be anywhere! 

If you know me you know I grew up in the countryyyy, loved every second of it, and am truly inspired by my small home town. This church is down the street from my parents and on a good Sunday they have 9 people in attendance. The Midwest always feel so nostalgic to me and I wanted to embrace that feeling so bringing some life back to this type of wedding style felt right. 

When I told my girls what I wanted to do they of course brought my vision to life in a way better than what was in my head. ILYSM @flowerdisco_ @rivieracreative_ @nataliegraycreative 

Also peep this new dress from @daughtersofsimone and the incredible earrings from @a.b.ellie 😍😍😍 two of my fav designers.

Also also how adorable is this cake?! @rosie_acres_bakery is a small bakery down the street who made this for us and she is just incredible at her craft! Locals please go check her out 🍰

It’s truly hard to pick which ones to share from Julie and Zane’s wedding. They were absolutely the funnest and most unique couple I had the pleasure of shooting. What I appreciated most was that their day was truly about them and what they wanted it to look like. 

They’re both avid burning man goers and every year essentially have their own party on their property in the mountains. They included so many creative hand made details like their giant bubble blowing bear or their glass fog blowing fox. 

This wedding was such an honor to be apart of and witness a wedding held in such a beautiful and intentional way. So much love for these two ❤️ 🌈 

Also shout out to @revelandbloom, Elise is such a baddie. One of the best planners I’ve worked with

A couple weeks ago I met up with Carly and Abe and we shot their engagements while walking around their neighborhood in the city. We stopped at spots that stuck out to me. There was no rhyme or reason and it felt perfect. I CANNOT wait to show you the magic that their wedding is going to be this fall. They have the best style and the funnest personalities. Counting down the days for it ❤️

Still loving this sweet intimate wedding between Kait and JJ. 

They were both some of my absolute favorite clients I’ve had. JJ is the sweetest angel boy and my girl Kait is just 🤌🏻 a vibe. They jumped in the pool after the ceremony then Kait decided to do a little chip chop on her hair. The whole day was just so fun, beautiful, and truly an honor to have been apart of it!
The Dolomites with Paiton and Joseph on film 🍋
Some film moments of my bestie and her husband while in Italy. @flowerdisco_ I cherish you more than you knowww 🤌🏻❤️

When she’s mommy but also mammi 😘

Ok but really Nick and I weren’t supposed to be the models but we were 🫣 

I was actually a little stressed this day but I’m actually selfishly very grateful we were the ones who stepped in because Nick and I have no photos together 😂 and this day was our 9 year wedding anniversary, so it was really special.

Sharing a few incredible images from two of my Italy gals who I love so dearly. Thank you for making me feel like a baddie ILYSM @randirobertsphoto @irisandoakphotography

Some film moments from my time in the city with Carly and Abe for their courthouse ceremony. 

This was my first time shooting a courthouse wedding and I’m enamored that it was with Carly and Abe. Carly is my fashionista bride of the year. So intentional with every piece (you’ll see more when I share from their wedding day) Both Carly and Abe are people I feel like I could just chat with for hours. Fell in love with them both 🥹 

Excited to share more with you from their wedding!

Part 1 of my incredible girls wedding with her guy in Santorini. 

I had the absolute honor of capturing Keely and Matt. There were so many incredible intentional details that made their day absolutely stunning but it was truly something special to witness the intimate group of people who came from all over to celebrate them. 

Feeling so fortunate to get to have had this experience but also so lucky to have this girl in my circle. Love you sweet Keely girl.
Some of my favorite moments from Melissa and Andy’s perfect intimate wedding in Tulum with one of my favorite wedding dresses I’ve shot by @moniquelhuillierbride 💕

Still really loving harsh daylight sessions 😍 

This session didn’t turn out in any way I way hoping but it’s important to learn to roll with the punches and work with what you’re given. 

As always, so thankful for my girls for making beautiful things for me @rivieracreative_ @nataliegray_styles @flowerdisco_ ❤️

I love posing. I love sensual. I loved this a lot.

Video by my talented girl @kpvisuals__
New headshots or whatever.

Comment “119” and I’ll send you the full episode with @fromthedaisies where she breaks down a truckload of wisdom about running Meta Ads to get inquiries and bookings as a photographer. LOVED this episode. 

#Weddingphotography #weddingphotographer #photographyeducation #photographytips #photographybusiness

Sharing a few of my favorite marigold moments with my favorite boys, Tyle and Austin 

I shot at this warehouse for a previous clients engagement session (remember the fun mattress one? My ogs know) but anyways I knew I needed to come back and give this space a flower moment. Of course my girl @flowerdisco_ brought this vision to life and then some 😍 

We all know I’m no stranger to butcher paper (again, my ogs know) and my incredibly talented girl @rivieracreative_ created the most beautiful table incorporating my favorite texture piece! 

It was so fun to create this and showcase the elements that are possible for your wedding day. 

K that’s all. LOVE YA.

Christmas in NYC, is there anything better🎄 

Styling: @nataliegray_styles 
Camcorder: @carterperry.co

A little break from my usual content to spam you with my snow angel babies, Stevie and Saint ♥️🛷

I had a lot of questions about this one when I shared in my stories. I shot this with my canon 5D mark IV with my flash (which you all know by now I love in harsh light) 

I know there are a handful out there that have shot with flash in daylight because I’ve *maybe* pressured you to 😂 but would love to know, do you love it? Hate it? Have you tried it yet?! It’s one of my absolute fav things to experiment with!

♥️ This was such a great wedding to end the year with. I’m always so inspired when I’m in New Orleans and being able to capture Emma and Rodney in this atmosphere was just truly such a gift. ♥️ 

I was so drawn to everything about Emma! Her style is obviously just so incredible but her whole demeanor was fun to shoot. Rodney also being the fashion king himself works for Prada so I mean, naturally, we connected ;) 

I love a couple that trusts me and they really did which allowed us to explore a little making it really hard to only share 10 frames from this day. So stayed tuned for a part 2 because I’m already just so in love!
published wedding photographer. Digital and Film. Documentary approach. Editorial feel.
